How to install Junos Pulse for VPN Connect

I. Install Junos Pulse on Windows:

Tutorial here:

https://www.net.usf.edu/vpn/Windows/

Snippet from the tutorial:

Surface Pro Users

At this time there is a known issue with the Pulse client and Windows Surface Pro and Pro2 tablets. Please do not proceed if you use a Windows Surface device.

 

Windows 10 Users

Currently the 5.0 release of the Junos Client does not support Windows 10. Windows 10 users are advised to uninstall the Junos Pulse client and install the new Pulse Secure Desktop Client version 5.1. This installer can be downloaded here (64-bit) or here (32-bit). 

Windows Vista, 7.x, 8.x Users

If you run into problems with the automatic install, you can try these instructions instead:

  • Download Junos Pulse for 64-bit Windows (typically Windows 7 and Windows 8) or Download Junos Pulse for 32-bit Windows (typically Windows XP).
  • Run the downloaded JunosPulse.x64.msi or JunosPulse.x86.msi file (double-click).
  • If the Pulse Client didn’t start automatically, find the Pulse icon in the system tray; note that it may be hidden by default and you may have to click the arrow in the system tray to expand the hidden icons.
  • Select the + symbol on the top right to add a connection.
  • Enter USF under Name: and vpn.usf.edu under Server URL:.
  • Leave the Type: as the default (UAC or SSL-VPN).
  • Click Add.
  • Click on the Connect button.
  • Enter your NetID under User Name: and your NetID password under Password:, then click on Connect.
  • A pop-up window will show after successful connection. The Junos Pulse VPN client will be visible and accessible as an icon in the system tray. If the icon has a green check mark, the VPN connection is active. You can disconnect and reconnect by clicking on the icon. Remember that the icon may be hidden, and you may have to click on the arrow to expand the system tray view.
  • If you have trouble connecting make sure that your possibly existing Network Connect client is not already connected. Reboot your machine, and without going to the vpn.usf.edu web site, attempt to connect from the system tray icon instead.
  • If you want to use the vpn.usf.edu web interface, please use Internet Explorer as the browser to launch the VPN client. Once the client has launched, you can switch to another browser of your choice if you prefer.

If you do not want the Pulse client to automatically load on startup, you can disable it by following these instructions.

II. Install Junos Pulse on Max OS:

turorail here: https://www.net.usf.edu/vpn/MacOS/

Snipet from the toturial:

OS X 10.11 El Capitan Users

The Old Junos Pulse Client (v. 4.0) is not supported on El Capitan. Users are advised to uninstall the Junos Pulse client and install the new Pulse Secure Desktop Client version 5.1. This installer can be downloaded here. 

OS X 10.10 or below

If you have not yet installed this new client, please follow the instructions below

  1. Download Junos Pulse for MacOS X
  2. Open the downloaded JunosPulse.dmg file (double-click) and run the JunosPulse.mpkg installer (double-click).
    1. If the installation fails due to an unidentified developer error, right-click on the NetworkConnect.mpkg file and select Open With > Installer.app (Default). 
    2. Select Open.
  3. Start Junos Pulse from the Applications folder.
  4. Select the + symbol on the bottom left to add a connection.
  5. Enter USF under Name: and vpn.usf.edu under Server URL:.
  6. Click on the orange Connect button.
  7. Enter your NetID under User Name: and your NetID password under Password:, then click on Connect. 
  8. A pop-up window will show after successful connection. The Junos Pulse VPN client will be visible and accessible as an icon in the menu bar. If the icon has a green check mark, the VPN connection is active. You can disconnect and reconnect by clicking on the icon.
  9. If you have trouble connecting make sure that your possibly existing Network Connect client is not already connected. Reboot your machine, and without going to the vpn.usf.edu web site, attempt to connect from the menu bar icon instead.
  10. If you’re using “Back to my mac” on your computer the VPN may not work. Please contact the Help Desk if you require this functionality.

Launching Pulse from the Web Interface

As an alternative to the above instructions, you can launch the Pulse client from the VPN web interface. To do so, please follow these instructions:

  • Use Safari to browse to vpn.usf.edu
  • Log in and click on the Start button by Junos Pulse (the first attempt will fail).
  • You will see a page similar to the one below. Do not yet click on any of the links
  • Open Safari Preferences, click the Security tab and choose Manage Website Settings… next to the Internet Plug-ins checkbox.
  • Click on Java and find the vpn.usf.edu URL listed in the right column. Change the pulldown for that listing to “Run in unsafe mode”. Click Done.
  • Click on the Once the setup client is installed -option highlighted below. You do not need to click on the setup client installation link.
  • Once Pulse has installed and connected, you’ll be returned to the initial VPN page. This is not an indication of failure.
  • You can see the VPN status in the menu bar.
